# Festag — popup header + body

Popups use a **large H1 that is already the sentence(s)** (1–3 calm sentences), then a **T1 body** underneath. Do **not** use a short label title plus a separate explanatory line.

## Do

```tsx
<h2 className="…-title">
  Setze dein Passwort oder deinen PIN zurück, oder schreib uns — wir helfen dir weiter.
</h2>
<div className="…-body">
  <p>Wähle unten, wie du wieder Zugang bekommen willst.</p>
  {/* fields / actions */}
</div>
```

Reference sizes (AuthSecurityModal / AuthPanelSwitchModal / AuthRecoveryModal):

| Token | Desktop | Mobile (≤768) |
|---|---|---|
| **H1** title (sentence) | `26px` / lh `1.28` | `28px` / lh `1.22` |
| **T1** body | `15.5px` / lh `1.65` | `16px` / lh `1.62` |

- **Light T1:** `#5c5c62` or `--fp-muted` on light surfaces
- **Dark T1:** `rgba(245,245,247,0.68)` or `--fp-muted`
- Overlay dismiss hint: **„Durch Klicken schließen.“** on first backdrop hover

## Don't

- Short Zwischenüberschrift titles (`Zugang wiederfinden`, `Client Panel`, `Passwort zurücksetzen`) with the real sentence only as muted body
- Muted second H1 line / stacked subtitle under a label title
- Small T0/eyebrow / kicker above or between H1 and T1
- Page `h1` leads on routes — those stay forbidden (`festag-no-page-leads`)

## Distinguish

| Surface | Under title |
|---|---|
| Page `h1` | **No** lead |
| Popup / sheet / modal | **Yes** — H1 = sentence(s), T1 = next calm sentence, then fields |
| Kickers | Still **no** |
| Middle dots in meta | Still **no** |
